{"cursor":"10337","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Weapon\n| name = Spencer Repeating Rifle image = caption = Spencer repeating rifle\n| origin = type = Manually cocked Lever Action Rifle\n\n| is_ranged = yes is_UK =\n\n| service = used_by = United States Army United States Navy Confederate\n| States of America Japan Empire of Brazil wars = American Civil\n| War Indian Wars Boshin War Paraguayan War\n\n| designer = Christopher Spencer design_date = 1860| manufacturer = Spencer\n| company, Burnside Rifle Co, Winchester unit_cost\n| = production_date = 1860â1869 number = 200,000 approx. variants =\n\n| spec_label = weight = length = rifle with 30 inch barrel carbine with 22\n| inch barrel http://www.romanorifle.com/html/spencer.html part_length\n| = The M-1863 version The M-1865 version width =\n| height = diameter = crew =\n\n| cartridge = .56-56 Spencer rimfire caliber = barrels = action = Manually\n| cocked hammer, lever action rate = 14 or 20 rounds per minute velocity = range = 500 yards max_range =\n| feed = 7 round tube magazine sights =\n}}\n\nThe 'Spencer repeating rifle' was a manually operated lever-action, repeating\nrifle fed from a tube magazine with cartridges. It was adopted by the Union\nArmy, especially by the cavalry, during the American Civil War, but did not\nreplace the standard issue muzzle-loading rifled muskets in use at the time. The\n'Spencer carbine' was a shorter and lighter version.\n","linknr":219,"url":"Spencer_repeating_rifle","recorded":1375090477,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Spencer_repeating_rifle&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Spencer_repeating_rifle&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2